# Sandbox Rules

## Container Setup
- Non-root user (uid 1000)
- Read-only rootfs
- Writable workspace volume only
- /tmp as tmpfs (size limited)
- No capabilities (drop ALL, add minimum)

## Resource Limits
- CPU: 1 core default, 4 max
- Memory: 512MB default, 4GB max
- Disk: 1GB writable
- Pids: 100
- Open files: 1024

## Network
- Default: no egress
- Allowlist mode for specific domains (V2)
- No internal network access

## Security Profiles
- seccomp: default + custom denylist
- apparmor: docker-default-restricted
- No privileged mode
- No host PID/IPC namespace

## Filesystem
- Workspace mount: /workspace (rw)
- /tmp: tmpfs, 100MB
- Everything else: ro

## Execution
- Timeout: 5 min default, 30 min max
- Output size limit: 10MB
- Stream stdout/stderr
- Capture exit code

## Command Filtering
- Deny: rm -rf /, fork bombs, mount, mkfs
- Deny: nc, ncat, socat (network tools)
- Deny: privileged binaries
- Allow list for shell commands per user role

## Lifecycle
- Auto-stop after idle (30 min)
- Cleanup on user logout
- Periodic garbage collection
- Limit concurrent runtimes per user

## Monitoring
- Track CPU/memory usage
- Alert on quota approach
- Log all exec calls
- Session recording (optional)